### Crawler Dynamic Rendering Failure

While running the crawler on:

```text
https://leetcode.com/contest/weekly-contest-511
```

the output reached:

```text
Entered crawl()
Inside while loop
Before fetch
after fetch
Framework detected
Dynamic framework detected
createTab FAILED
```

The crawler successfully fetched the URL and detected a dynamic framework, but RenderEngine failed to create a CDP tab.

I checked the Chrome DevTools Protocol endpoint:

```bash
curl http://localhost:9222/json/version
```

The result was:

```text
curl: (7) Failed to connect to localhost port 9222
Could not connect to server
```

This confirmed that Chrome was not running with remote debugging enabled.

### Permanent RenderEngine Solution

`RenderEngine::createTab()` depends on:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:9222/json/new?<url>
```

Therefore, Chrome must be running with:

```text
--remote-debugging-port=9222
```

Instead of manually starting Chrome every time, the permanent solution was to make RenderEngine manage Chrome/CDP availability.

The intended workflow became:

```text
Check CDP availability
        |
        v
Is port 9222 available?
    |             |
   Yes            No
    |             |
    |       Launch Chrome
    |             |
    |       Wait for CDP
    |             |
    +-------------+
          |
          v
      Create Tab
          |
          v
 WebSocket Connection
          |
          v
    Rendered HTML
```

This allowed the crawler to handle dynamic pages without requiring manual Chrome startup before every run.

### RenderEngine Testing Errors

After RenderEngine started working, GoogleTest cases were created.

The first build failed with:

```text
collect2.exe: error: ld returned 1 exit status
```

An incorrect CMake configuration attempted to link the test against the main `Crawler` executable.

CMake reported:

```text
Target "Crawler" of type EXECUTABLE
may not be linked into another target.
```

The test was changed to compile the required implementation directly:

```cmake
add_executable(renderengine_test
    testing/renderengine_testing.cpp
    src/renderengine.cpp
)
```

Another error occurred when using:

```cmake
CURL::libcurl
```

CMake reported:

```text
Target "renderengine_test" links to CURL::libcurl
but the target was not found.
```

The test configuration was changed to match the project's existing CURL and Boost setup.

After fixing the CMake configuration:

```text
All RenderEngine test cases passed.
```

