## Section 5 — Learning Reflection

The main change in my understanding was that passing basic tests does not mean a component is robust.

HTMLParser edge tests exposed assumptions that normal test cases did not reveal.

I learned that tests must match the actual API design, especially the difference between static and non-static methods.

PageStorage testing showed me that database tests are integration tests because they depend on MySQL, schema state, and environment configuration.

The most important RenderEngine learning was that CDP is a separate runtime dependency.

Chrome being installed does not mean port `9222` is available.

helped confirm that the problem was CDP availability rather than crawler logic.

I also learned that the RenderEngine should manage Chrome/CDP availability instead of requiring manual startup.

Finally, I learned an important CMake design rule: an executable should not be used as a reusable library.

